paragraphs.title: Load Parquet File and Cache it, Show 2 Rows
Process Date/Time Columns to Have Rich Features
paragraphs.text:
val format = new java.text.SimpleDateFormat("MM/dd/yyyyHH:mm")
import java.util.Calendar

case class RichDate(date: java.sql.Date, monthDay: String, year: Int, month: Int, day: Int, dayOfYear: Int, dayInWeek: Int, hour: Int, minute: Int)

val udfDate = udf[RichDate, String, String]((d,t) => {
    val date = format.parse(d+t)
    val calendar = Calendar.getInstance
    calendar.setTime(date)
    
    RichDate(
        new java.sql.Date(date.getTime()), 
        d.take(5),
        calendar.get(Calendar.YEAR), 
        calendar.get(Calendar.MONTH), 
        calendar.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH), 
        calendar.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_YEAR),
        calendar.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_WEEK),
        calendar.get(Calendar.HOUR_OF_DAY),
        calendar.get(Calendar.MINUTE))
})

val dfRich=df.
    withColumn("RichDate", udfDate($"Date", $"Time")).
    drop("Date").
    withColumn("date", $"RichDate.date").
    withColumn("year", $"RichDate.year").
    withColumn("month", $"RichDate.month").
    withColumn("monthDay", $"RichDate.monthDay").
    withColumn("day", $"RichDate.day").
    withColumn("dayInWeek", $"RichDate.dayInWeek").
    withColumn("dayOfYear", $"RichDate.dayOfYear").
    withColumn("hour", $"RichDate.hour").
    withColumn("minute", $"RichDate.minute")

paragraphs.title: Week Day Hour Heat map
paragraphs.text:
val category = z.select("Category", "FRAUD", categories.map(s => (s, s))).toString

highcharts(dfRich.filter($"Category" === category)
  .series("x" -> "dayInWeek", "y" -> "hour", "value" -> count("*")).orderBy($"dayInWeek", $"hour")
  ).chart(Chart.heatmap)("colorAxis", "stops", stops).title(s"Reports $category During the Week").xAxis(new XAxis("day").typ("category")).plot
